    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/1–3048: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Cuba</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 30, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>132. Personal for Wilcox from Brown. Have received direct question from French
                    and British <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>s whether we expect obtain
                    Congressional <pb facs="0349" n="839" xml:id="pg_839"/> action Charter this
                    session and whether Administration will request action this session. Have
                    replied that because delay completion Charter Habana beyond first February and
                    unanticipatedly slow progress Marshall plan, believe most unlikely Congress will
                    act this session. Decision Administration present Charter will depend situation
                    Congress at end Habana conference and character Charter which emerges.
                    [Brown.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
